# API Design
- RESTful conventions: GET /resources, POST /resources, GET /resources/:id
- Status codes: 200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 401 Unauthorized, 404 Not Found, 500 Server Error
- Consistent response envelope: { success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }
- Pagination: cursor-based for infinite scroll, offset for tables
- Filtering, sorting, searching via query params

# Database
- Use ORM (Drizzle/Prisma) or query builder — NO raw SQL strings
- Migrations: version-controlled, reversible, tested
- Index foreign keys and frequently queried columns
- N+1 query prevention: eager load related data

# Authentication & Authorization
- JWT access tokens (short-lived: 15min) + refresh tokens (long-lived: 7days)
- RBAC: Role-based access control middleware
- Middleware stack: Auth → Validation → Rate Limit → Handler

# Error Handling
- Centralized error handler middleware
- Operational errors (400s) vs Programmer errors (500s)
- Structured logging: timestamp, requestId, userId, error stack
- NEVER expose internal error details to client in production

# Validation
- Zod schemas for ALL inputs (path params, query, body)
- Validate at the boundary (controller level), not in business logic
- Custom error messages for user-facing validation
